article.headline: Cleveland St. 68, Youngstown St. 55
article.story: CLEVELAND (AP) -- Raheem Moss scored 21 points and Cleveland State rode an 11-0 first-half run to a 68-55 victory over Youngstown State on Saturday night. Bahaadar Russell and J'Nathan Bullock each added 11 points for the Vikings (10-20, 3-13 Horizon League). Byron Davis had 15 points, Jack Liles 14 and John Barber 11 for Youngstown State (13-16, 7-9). Quin Humphrey scored only eight points but still finished as the Horizon League's leading scorer for the second year in a row. The Vikings led 7-2 at the outset and was on top 19-14 before the Penguins ran off seven consecutive points for a 21-19 lead, the last bucket by Liles. Cleveland State then went on an 11-0 run and was ahead 37-27 at the half. Moss scored five points and Bullock had four in the spurt. The lead never fell below five points in the second half.
